"Do I Know This Already?" Quiz

5. The correct answer is A, not B.  Setting icmp_echo_ignore_all to 1 will
block "ping" (i.e. ICMP echo) packets but not other ICMP packets.

icmp_echo_ignore_broadcasts defaults to 1 in RHEL 7, which blocks broadcast
pings, but unicast pings are still allowed through unless blocked by
icmp_echo_ignore_all or a firewall rule.

Exercise 28.2:

7. The filename should be /etc/sysctl.d/ping.conf, not ping.-conf
